cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC

This paper proposes a cooperative mechanism for mitigating the performance degradation due to non-IID data in collaborative machine learning, specifically federated learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) since the proposed mechanism is designed for wireless networks. The paper also involves heuristic algorithms for client- and data-selection, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper deals with the aggregation of models, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
